criteria.textblock:
        Inclusion Criteria:

          1. Objectively proven (as previously described (8)) proximal idiopathic deep vein
             thrombosis or pulmonary embolism. Idiopathic will be defined as VTE occurring in the
             absence of fracture, plaster cast, immobilization greater than 3 days or a general
             anesthetic in the last three months prior to VTE diagnosis; a known deficiency of
             antithrombin, protein C or protein S; and malignancy in the last five years

          2. Patients treated initially with a minimum of five days of heparin or low molecular
             weight heparin and oral anticoagulants with a target intensity of 2.0 - 3.0 with no
             recurrence in the subsequent six months.

          3. Patients currently on oral anticoagulants

        Exclusion Criteria:

          1. Recurrent idiopathic VTE (i.e. &#8805; 2 previous idiopathic VTE). Previous secondary
             VTE is not an exclusion criterion;

          2. Age &lt;18;

          3. Known deficiency of proteins S, protein C or antithrombin;

          4. Known, persistently positive anticardiolipin antibodies (titers &gt; 30U/ml);

          5. Known, persistently positive lupus anticoagulant;

          6. Combined thrombophilic defects (e.g. homozygous for FVL or PGM, or compound
             heterozygous for FVL and PGM);

          7. Refusal of informed consent.
